lcm09ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwiaW50ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLC=
JsaW5rX2lkIjoyMDQzMTk0fQ/e61c30930ba0f3ba44346ddf2276f459f0da8bea910fa25aa1=
2748118431903d" style=3D"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">offered<=
/a> viewers a nice balance between semi-scripted playfulness (=E2=80=9CSame=
 push=E2=80=A6 different tush=E2=80=9D) and insight. At one point in the fi=
rst half, Eagles quarterback <strong>Jalen Hurts</strong> changed the play =
call three times at the line of scrimmage, and Brady translated the audible=
s as they were
unfolding.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">There were also a couple other interes=
ting moments of rare Brady <em>humanitas</em>, which has been lacking this =
season. Late in the game, he half-joked that he would <em>not </em>have sli=
d, as <strong>Saquon Barkley </strong>did while running for a first down in=
 the fourth quarter, to avoid running up the score while running out the cl=
ock. Secondly, Brady seemed mildly apoplectic about
<strong>Jordan Love</strong>=E2=80=99s slightly inaccurate throw to the fla=
t on fourth down during the closing minutes of the contest. Most analysts w=
ould have blamed the receiver for an inability to get his feet down in boun=
ds, but Brady laid the blame on the QB, expressing disbelief that Love had =
<em>ever so slightly </em>missed his target.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;=
margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">So, =
why is Brady only getting a B-? Well, dear reader, let me tell
you a story about <strong>Jason Witten</strong>, the former Cowboys tight e=
nd who spent a single season as a <em>Monday Night Football</em> analyst in=
 2018. To this day, Witten is known for mangling idioms, <strong>Yogi Berra=
</strong>-style, like the time he said that <strong>Aaron Rodgers</strong> =
pulled a rabbit out of his head or his analysis that the 49ers were kicking=
 themselves in the foot. The gaffes really weren=E2=80=99t <em>that</em> ba=
d, but they took on a life of their own and eventually
became the defining narrative of his brief tenure in the booth.</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">I recalle=
d Witten=E2=80=99s year of magical thinking <em>several </em>times yesterda=
y, like when Brady referred to Packers running back <strong>Josh Jacobs</st=
rong> as <strong>Brandon</strong> <strong>Jacobs</strong> (the old Giants b=
ack who defeated Brady in two Super Bowls) or when he misidentified Hurts a=
s Love (or was it a two-time divorc=C3=A9=E2=80=99s subconscious cry for
help?) or when he mistakenly referred to the Eagles as the Phillies (too ma=
ny avocado smoothies, Tommy?). Sure, they=E2=80=99re small mistakes, but my=
 social feeds and texts blew up with each one of them. Knowing Brady, I exp=
ect he=E2=80=99ll watch the film, be as critical of himself as he was about=
 Love on fourth down, and clean things up. As for now, he=E2=80=99s on to D=
etroit with a gentleman=E2=80=99s B.</p></div>
