because it recently signed <em>glide path </em>deals with distributors incl=
uding DirecTV and Charter. If YES gives in to Comcast=E2=80=99s demands, Di=
recTV and Charter <em>could </em>press for the same terms. Also, YES=E2=80=
=99s previous Comcast deals all stipulated that it would remain in the same=
 tier as SNY, which carries the Mets and happens to be partly owned by Comc=
ast. While that affiliation may not mean much any longer in terms of preser=
ving rights, SNY is in the middle of a long-term deal with
Comcast.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"=
margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Nevertheless, YES executives know the Comcast =
